  "doc_id": "28249",
  "text": "Higher azimuthal modes can be obtained similarly asΨ which is defined by D ± m ≡ e −i(m±1)φ (ǫ ± · ∇) e imφ , where ǫ + = ǫ, and ǫ − = ǫ * is the complex conjugate of ǫ. The calculation of (A 3) is algebraically complicated but can be done by the computer algebra system Mathematica [CITATION_1] , which requires considerable computer resources and practically can be carried out only for m ≤ 5. But this suffices to deduce the general solution (3.4).",
